            "answer_text": "Since [math]f(x+y)= f(xy) [/math]for any [math]x[/math] and [math]y[/math] belonging to the set of real numbers. Putting [math]y=1, [/math]we have [math]f(x+1)=f(x).[/math] A constant function is a periodic function with fundamental period 1, thus for a constant function: [math]f(x+1)=f(x).[/math] Hence proven ",
